Definition.WordDefinition: Carline \Car"line\, Caroline \Car"o*line\, n. [F. carin; cf. It. carlino; -- so called from Carlo (Charles) VI. of Naples.] A silver coin once current in some parts of Italy, worth about seven cents. --Simmonds. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: Caroline \Car"o*line\, n. A coin. See {Carline}. [1913 Webster]
Caroline adj : of or relating to the life and times of kings Charles I or Charles II of England [syn: {Carolean}]
